// This project 


Step 1:Clone the repository

Step 2: Install the virtualenv:
py -m pip install --user virtualenv


Step 3: create  a virtual environment:
py -m venv env

Step 4: Activate the virtual environment:
.\env\Scripts\activate

Step 5: Browse to "myProject" directory of the downloaded project using command prompt:

cd myProject

Step 6: Install requirements.I have already generated the requirements.txt file:
pip install -r requirements.txt

Step 7: Run the server locally:
python3 manage.py runserver

Step 8: Enter the following link on your browser:
http://127.0.0.1:8000


